a.xlink:title: The Discovery class describes how an incident was detected.
A free-form text description of how this incident was detected.

Categorizes the techniques used to discover the incident. These values are partially derived from Table 3-1 of [NIST800.61rev2]. These values are maintained in the "Discovery- source" IANA registry per Section 10.2.
A means by which to extend the source attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
See Section 3.3.1.
A means by which to extend the restriction attribute. See Section 5.1.1.

The Contact class describes contact information for organizations and personnel involved in the incident. This class allows for the naming of the involved party, specifying contact information for them, and identifying their role in the incident.
The name of the contact. The contact may either be an organization or a person. The type attribute disambiguates the semantics.
The title for the individual named in the ContactName.
A free-form text description of the contact.
The timezone in which the contact resides.
A mechanism by which to extend the data model.
A means by which to extend the role attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
A means by which to extend the type attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
See Section 3.3.1.
A means by which to extend the restriction attribute. See Section 5.1.1.

The DetectionPattern class describes a configuration or signature that can be used by an Intrusion Detection System (IDS) / Intrusion Prevention System (IPS), SIEM, antivirus, endpoint protection, network analysis, malware analysis, or host forensics tool to identify a particular phenomenon. This class requires the identification of the target application and allows the configuration to be described in either free form or machine-readable form.
The application for which the DetectionConfiguration or Description is being provided.
A free-form text description of how to use the information provided in the Application or DetectionConfiguration classes.
A machine-consumable configuration to find a pattern of activity.
See Section 3.3.1.
A means by which to extend the restriction attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
See Section 3.3.2.
The RegistryHandle class represents a handle into an Internet registry or community-specific database.
The PostalAddress class specifies a postal address and associated annotation.
A postal address.
A free-form text description of the address.
Categorizes the type of address described in the PAddress class. These values are maintained in the "PostalAddress-type" IANA registry per Section 10.2.
A means by which to extend the type attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
The Email class specifies an email address and associated annotation.
An email address.
A free-form text description of the email address.
Categorizes the type of email address described in the EmailTo class. These values are maintained in the "Email- type" IANA registry per Section 10.2.
A means by which to extend the type attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
The Telephone class describes a telephone number and associated annotation.
A telephone number.
A free-form text description of the phone number.
Categorizes the type of telephone number described in the TelephoneNumber class. These values are maintained in the "Telephone-type" IANA registry per Section 10.2.
A means by which to extend the type attribute. See Section 5.1.1.
